gc.pmb_library.android.api.interfaces
Interface PMB

All Known Implementing Classes:
PMBManager
public interface PMB

The Interface PMB.

Author:
Carsten Fasold
Copyright 2012 GrandCentrix GmbH.
All rights reserved.
This interface provides the methods: to start the PushNotification from the PushMeBaby Server get,set and delete the tags or the Quiet Time from the PushMeBaby Server

Method Detail

startPMB

void startPMB(android.content.Context context,
              UDID UDIDImpl)
              throws PMBException
Starts the PushMeBaby Service. It should be the first thing that gets called. This method is called with no username so the username would be set as undefined at the PushMeBaby Server.

Parameters:
context - the context of the Application
UDIDImpl - the own implementation of the UDID class. If it is zero, the default implementation is used
Throws:
PMBException - this class is the main class for all Exceptions.You can get the ErrorText with .getErrorText or you grab, with .getException, the real Exception e.g. JSONException an print the Stack for example

startPMB

void startPMB(android.content.Context context,
              UDID UDIDImpl,
              java.lang.String user)
              throws PMBException
Starts the PushMeBaby Service. It should be the first thing that gets called. This method is called with the username so the username would be set as the given name at the PushMeBaby Server.

Parameters:
context - the context of the Application
UDIDImpl - the own implementation of the UDID class. If it is zero, the default implementation is used
user - The username
